document.title: Tennessee Academic Standards: Mathematics K-4th Year

115728DEE1844136879FFE095A936536.description: Explain the differences between correlation and causation. Recognize situations where an additional factor may be affecting correlated data.

3A5E9FD9561444AF82B4B0345DD3FD09.description: Use technology to compute the correlation coefficient of a linear model; interpret the correlation coefficient in the context of the data.

351632ECE088457BAECF68A03A783BEA.description: Interpret the rate of change and the constant term of a linear model in the context of the data.

766CDA60337D4F8EB2B71548782422FE.description: Represent data from two quantitative variables on a scatter plot, and describe how the variables are related. Fit a function to the data; use functions fitted to data to solve problems in the context of the data.

546746E673664AEE8F26F0F689BDA03E.description: Summarize, represent, and interpret data on two categorical and quantitative variables.

D490A42E85F84143B692191364DE9C83.description: Understand the relationship between the Pythagorean Theorem and the distance formula and use an efficient method to solve problems on the coordinate plane.

9DEDA3A81B7B4A11BCE2FFC1D240FA39.description: Use the slope criteria for parallel and perpendicular lines to solve problems and to justify relationships in geometric figures.

B2BB88D1B6AA4E24A43CE54D11CA8436.description: Use coordinates to solve problems and justify geometric relationships algebraically.

EDEE3002AED4453E970DAB862881F17F.description: Use coordinates to solve problems and justify simple geometric theorems algebraically.

9FD705200F92471AA07147D2E111A5ED.description: Use geometric constructions to solve geometric problems in context, by hand and using technology.

E4AA05219FC8491CB75ADC165DB19EDF.description: Perform formal geometric constructions with a variety of tools and methods (compass and straightedge, string, reflective devices, paper folding, dynamic geometric software, etc.).

167205BAEF96447C8E7A97EF2B53DECE.description: Use definitions and theorems about triangles to solve problems and to justify relationships in geometric figures.

9450C1FBCDEB40B2B47C4172CBCA0B36.description: Use definitions and theorems about lines and angles to solve problems and to justify relationships in geometric figures.

284EA9CACFF84A79A952496D44C13D72.description: Use geometric theorems to justify relationships.

9CE2ACDA7FC24FF79F263C0B52A66102.description: Given a rectangle, parallelogram, trapezoid, or regular polygon, determine the transformations that carry the shape onto itself and describe them in terms of the symmetry of the figure.

002CC79D0513473CACC2F54BD5DBE2A8.description: Describe transformations as functions that take points in the plane (pre-image) as inputs and give other points (image) as outputs. Compare transformations that preserve distance and angle measure to those that do not, by hand for basic transformations and using technology for more complex cases.

70161A2987F641F69FC870DCE1315263.description: Experiment with transformations in the plane.

B75C8D6157C04298AADE337E18E748C1.description: Interpret the parameters in a linear or exponential function in terms of a context.

4B11D528C7D14C2F8A6DF45E48F270E0.description: Interpret expressions for functions in terms of the situation they model.

C5914B971C3C4A3E88C483286C742BF8.description: Construct linear and exponential functions, including arithmetic and geometric sequences, given a graph, a table, a description of a relationship, or input-output pairs.

42899614C0884DC2A089AE85DFDAC0A9.description: Recognize situations in which a quantity grows or decays by a constant factor per unit interval relative to another.

5458175E8CD845EEADC8FD219FD3C3F9.description: Recognize situations in which one quantity changes at a constant rate per unit interval relative to another.

C23787BE8C874AF88B8297C51A54CBD1.description: Know that linear functions grow by equal differences over equal intervals and that exponential functions grow by equal factors over equal intervals.

C4BA2BD326194435BE692B7DC0FAACDD.description: Distinguish between situations that can be modeled with linear functions and with exponential functions.

C78B3CA053ED4D6499A6085E1E00FC27.description: Construct and compare linear and exponential models and solve problems.

983022437B6E4FDAA7DD6E6AEA68D4AC.description: Define sequences as functions, including recursive definitions, whose domain is a subset of the integers. Write explicit and recursive formulas for arithmetic and geometric sequences in context and connect them to linear and exponential functions.

0C5F2DA2EC0A471993B3E0B3D2CC5A10.description: Determine steps for calculation, a recursive process, or an explicit expression from a context.

1E808FE6D7BC4EB0A9A2B382B5E9CD0D.description: Build a function that describes a relationship between two quantities.

4C8202475579430396F7E80E13887D85.description: Build a function that models a relationship between two quantities.

348C9FAB087F46A4BB3B42FCBD7D48A4.description: Compare properties of the same function on two different intervals or represented in two different ways.

985175AC58DC44DEAFD5C9CCACA249EF.description: Compare properties of two different functions. Functions may be of different types and/or represented in different ways.

C87899220CFC41CB95243AB1ADA3FA04.description: Compare properties of functions represented algebraically, graphically, numerically in tables, or by verbal descriptions.

4F95CEA8464A41D6A316229AC9582F4D.description: Relate the domain of a function to its graph and, where applicable, to the context of the function it models.

649C4F1478F4459580CA41C7B43556E1.description: For a function that models a relationship between two quantities, interpret key features of graphs and tables in terms of the quantities, and sketch graphs showing key features given a verbal description of the relationship.

0C12BA26DC044DF89728C56DD0C3C019.description: Interpret functions that arise in applications in terms of the context.

3E9FF0BA80AD40CC8F8274DC541E4E67.description: Interpret statements that use function notation in terms of a context.

C9ABDA474FCD4A16B30E9DD478B9EF6E.description: Use function notation to evaluate functions for inputs in their domains, including functions of two variables.

8635700BCF634CB1B76C1EE395D7DCD6.description: Understand that a function from one set (called the domain) to another set (called the range) assigns to each element of the domain exactly one element of the range. If f is a function and x is an element of its domain, then f(x) denotes the output of f corresponding to the input x. The graph of f is the graph of the equation y = f(x).

2CF0A405475348AD95F2F55BEC94AE1F.description: Understand the concept of a function and use function notation.

21EADF094C614BE88E010F4F149E1024.description: Graph the solution set to a system of linear inequalities in two variables as the intersection of the corresponding halfplanes.

DEB01C0DD74C4C2EAC95CA95BBCA88CE.description: Explain why the x-coordinates of the points where the graphs of the equations y = f(x) and y = g(x) intersect are the solutions of the equation f(x) = g(x). Find approximate solutions by graphing the functions or making a table of values, using technology when appropriate.

F5060DFEFFC848C9A6CF6F590BF37458.description: Understand that the graph of an equation in two variables is the set of all its solutions plotted in the coordinate plane, often forming a curve (which could be a line).

F31958B2AAFF4625B044EA45A467D9A0.description: Represent and solve equations and inequalities graphically.

A98B223E032A435EA7F454999E66EB69.description: Write and solve a system of linear equations in a real-world context.

8A4C4D6293814AB0A6E60233CBCB3E61.description: Solve absolute value equations and inequalities in one variable. Represent solutions algebraically and graphically.

F23FBE60B78B46D98F94881CD24D7F13.description: Solve linear equations and inequalities, including compound inequalities, in one variable. Represent solutions algebraically and graphically.

E0C22063B2654092A16B98102BA1BCB3.description: Solve linear and absolute value equations and inequalities in one variable.

D4FECCD1AFD74F9995F96E0ADD18365F.description: Solve equations and inequalities in one variable.

03486C4C61F74F1AA63D9F6E18C2D84F.description: Understand solving equations as a process of reasoning and explain the reasoning. Construct a viable argument to justify a solution method.

3E68569C4CFE438AA9DACA14758D5D25.description: Understand solving equations as a process of reasoning and explain the reasoning.

40C9CB0FA3F8413ABAA6E8EBDAAA70A6.description: Rearrange formulas to isolate a quantity of interest using algebraic reasoning.

7493EEABD52C41EC937CA4C7CBD19A80.description: Create individual and systems of equations and/or inequalities to represent constraints in a contextual situation, and interpret solutions as viable or non-viable.

C9359D9462AE4AE78FAFFB83F8C8A211.description: Create equations and inequalities in two variables to represent relationships between quantities and use them to solve problems in a real-world context. Graph equations with two variables on coordinate axes with labels and scales, and use the graphs to make predictions.

BA62E7A833A240CD9330E0179B297144.description: Create equations and inequalities in one variable and use them to solve problems in a real-world context.

E74BB240F46341758CFF1D6F7CA27698.description: Create equations that describe numbers or relationships

CABE942129714674A50AC0D873B1FDB4.description: Interpret complicated expressions by viewing one or more of their parts as a single entity.

E22DB9F96EA34EBD935AB87DE582DF7A.description: Interpret parts of an expression, such as terms, factors, and coefficients.

001C9A7423D244E3BB884468B038DBAB.description: quantity in terms of its context.

2D24BE22DCDC4C799BA743404DFCD870.description: Create and use augmented matrices to solve systems of linear equations in real-world contexts, by hand and using technology.

ED06C98F1A8A442DA8E9D3A0A498877A.description: Describe the roles that zero matrices and identity matrices play in matrix addition and multiplication, recognizing that they are similar to the roles of 0 and 1 in the real number system.

552FA866F3DD431995D0F338C9C2419F.description: Multiply matrices of appropriate dimensions, by hand in simple cases and using technology for more complicated cases.

76B9654171F6440D9781D4D0D0052895.description: Add and/or subtract matrices by hand and using technology.

926ECE5D34AA4BC0910A11B5BBDE4E38.description: Multiply a matrix by a scalar to produce a new matrix.

07AB91BC8A1C447289CF12A0EEA06010.description: Perform operations on matrices in a real-world context.

5F5D8697D9A0474C970673A3B059831B.description: Use matrices to represent data in a real-world context. Interpret rows, columns, and dimensions of matrices in terms of the context.

366260B68ECD40B1BAAF42428A072825.description: Perform operations on matrices and use matrices in applications.

34B696E54A164A80BE528DA552451310.description: Choose an appropriate level of accuracy when reporting quantities.

D6FC16D90A7B4711AAD38BC19E83D096.description: Define and justify appropriate quantities within a context for the purpose of modeling.

D0018D243232480087B8932B1396269F.description: Use appropriate quantities in formulas, converting units as necessary.

E694C833E22D4192AD8B7F460ED9E650.description: Choose and interpret the scale and the origin in graphs and data displays.

490A12A050EE41E580405BFEDF51B04E.description: Use units as a way to understand real-world problems.

C4611149F7B142A39601CBCCA01330A6.description: Reason quantitatively and use units to understand problems.
